===Verb===
{{en-verb|plac|ing}}

# {{intransitive}} To earn a given spot in a competition.
# {{transitive}} To put (an object or person) in a specific location.
# {{transitive}} To [[remember]] [[where]] and [[when]] (an object or person) has been previously encountered.
#: ''I've seen him before, but I can't quite '''place''' where.''
# {{transitive}} (''in the passive'') To [[achieve]] (a certain [[position]], often followed by an ordinal) as in a horse race.
# {{transitive}} To [[sing]] (a note) with the correct [[pitch]].
# {{transitive}} To arrange for or to make (a bet).
# {{transitive}} To [[recruit]] or [[match]] an appropriate person for a [[job]].
#: ''They phoned hoping to '''place''' her in the management team.''

====Synonyms====
*(''put in a specific location''): [[deposit]], [[lay]], [[lay down]], [[put down]]
*(''remember where and when something or someone was previously encountered''):
*(''passive: achieve (a certain position'')): [[achieve]], [[make]]
*(''sing (a note) with the correct pitch''): [[reach]]
*(''arrange for, make (a bet'')):

